"{\"abstract\":\"In this paper, we propose an efficient method to reconstruct surface-from-gradients (SfG). Our method is formulated under the framework of discrete geometry processing. Unlike the existing SfG approaches, we transfer the continuous reconstruction problem into a discrete space and efficiently solve the problem via a sequence of least-square optimization steps. Our discrete formulation brings three advantages: 1) the reconstruction preserves sharp-features, 2) sparse/incomplete set of gradients can be well handled, and 3) domains of computation can have irregular boundaries. Our formulation is direct and easy to implement, and the comparisons with state-of-the-arts show the effectiveness of our method.\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"2358916\",\"name\":\"Wuyuan Xie\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/2358916\"},{\"authorId\":\"5537690\",\"name\":\"Y. Zhang\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/5537690\"},{\"authorId\":\"8206070\",\"name\":\"C. Wang\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/8206070\"},{\"authorId\":\"2054633\",\"name\":\"R. Chung\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/2054633\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"145916712\",\"name\":\"K. Han\"},{\"authorId\":\"1698116\",\"name\":\"K. Wong\"},{\"authorId\":\"65795460\",\"name\":\"Miaomiao Liu\"}],\"doi\":\"10.1007/s11263-017-1045-3\",\"intent\":[\"methodology\"],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"bffbaf65282d62cd594ef8fc6396a3d7f9dba899\",\"title\":\"Dense Reconstruction of Transparent Objects by Altering Incident Light Paths Through Refraction\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/bffbaf65282d62cd594ef8fc6396a3d7f9dba899\",\"venue\":\"International Journal of Computer Vision\",\"year\":2017},{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"2996189\",\"name\":\"Dongping Deng\"},{\"authorId\":\"35637603\",\"name\":\"Tsz-Ho Kwok\"},{\"authorId\":\"47558604\",\"